---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Pool Builders Mermaid Beach | Resurface & New Build | 0485 939 966"
  description="Swimming pool builders and resurfacing for Mermaid Beach — ageing 1980s–90s pebble pools needing quartz / tile refit, narrow-block fibreglass installs, salt-zone equipment specialists. Free quote."
  canonical="https://goldcoastpoolbuilders.com.au/mermaid-beach/">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Mermaid Beach &middot; Nobby Beach &middot; Miami</span>
      <h1>Pool builders &amp; resurfacers in <span class="accent">Mermaid Beach</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Mermaid Beach is one of the Gold Coast&rsquo;s original beachside suburbs &mdash;
        narrow 500&ndash;700m&sup2; blocks running back from Hedges Avenue and the
        Highway, mostly developed in the 1970s&ndash;90s with first-wave suburban pools.
        Half our local work here is resurfacing those ageing pebble pools; the other
        half is fibreglass installs squeezed into tight rear yards.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61485939966">&#9742; Call 0485 939 966</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free on-site quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Mermaid Beach</span>
      <h2>The Mermaid Beach pool story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Original pool stock right in the resurface window.</h3>
        <p>
          About <strong>60% of Mermaid Beach houses with pools have a 1980s or
          1990s concrete pool</strong> with an original pebble (Pebblecrete or
          Quartzon) interior. Pebble lifespan in a salt-chlorinator Gold Coast pool
          is 12&ndash;20 years; the original Mermaid Beach pool wave is now 25&ndash;40
          years old. Surfaces are sandpaper-rough, aggregate is pinning out, and
          rust streaks from corroding steel rebar are appearing. The fix is a
          full chip-off + bond + new interior in pebble, quartz or full mosaic
          tile. $9K&ndash;$22K (pebble/quartz) or $25K+ for tiled.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Narrow-block fibreglass crane access.</h3>
        <p>
          Mermaid Beach blocks typically have <strong>2m side setbacks on each side</strong>
          and an established palm or two between the house and the fence. That
          restricts crane access for fibreglass shell delivery to shells under
          ~8m. Most often that&rsquo;s fine &mdash; 7&ndash;8m fibreglass is a
          perfect family-pool size. But for larger shells we sometimes need to
          remove a section of side fence temporarily or coordinate with the
          neighbour, and very occasionally helicopter delivery is the only option
          (priced $5K&ndash;$10K extra).
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Glass fencing + ocean salt air.</h3>
        <p>
          Pool fencing on Mermaid Beach blocks faces direct ocean salt air. Standard
          aluminium balustrade hardware corrodes fast in this environment &mdash;
          we spec marine-grade 316 stainless or full powder-coated aluminium with
          stainless fixings, NOT the cheap 304 stainless that some installers
          use inland. Toughened glass is the same regardless. Hardware lifetime in
          salt air: 304 stainless 3&ndash;5 years (visible rust), 316 stainless
          12&ndash;15 years, premium-coated aluminium 15&ndash;20 years.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Mermaid Beach jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>1990s pebble pool resurface to quartz interior + new coping ($16K&ndash;$28K)</li>
          <li>7m fibreglass plunge pool with paving surround + glass fence ($55K&ndash;$75K turnkey)</li>
          <li>Equipment-only modernisation: variable-speed pump + new chlorinator + heat pump ($5K&ndash;$8K)</li>
          <li>Full pool renovation: resurface + new coping + new paving + new fence ($35K&ndash;$60K)</li>
          <li>Salt-rated equipment retrofit for ageing 1980s pool</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/burleigh-heads/">Burleigh Heads</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/mudgeeraba/">Mudgeeraba</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/robina/">Robina</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/helensvale/">Helensvale</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/city-of-gold-coast/">All City of Gold Coast</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Mermaid Beach on-site quote.</h2>
        <p>Narrow-block design that works. Honest resurface vs replace assessment for older pools.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61485939966">&#9742; Call 0485 939 966</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
